 And so I just, when I saw these two or three women with such absolute recoveries from just

00:17:38.900 --> 00:17:51.140
 small amounts of progesterone, I realized that I would be basically injuring people

00:17:51.140 --> 00:17:57.900
 that I talked to if I didn't give them the true information that I knew about in animals

00:17:57.900 --> 00:18:02.700
 and was starting to see in humans.

00:18:02.700 --> 00:18:10.940
 And so I would just mention what I saw was the case.

00:18:10.940 --> 00:18:21.220
 And over a period of, I guess, two or three years in Eugene, I had spoken to enough women

00:18:21.220 --> 00:18:31.140
 about the effects of thyroid and progesterone and their symptoms that the local gynecologists

00:18:31.140 --> 00:18:37.700
 had turned 180 degrees in their practice just because there were so many dozens of their

00:18:37.700 --> 00:18:45.940
 patients saying that they wouldn't take estrogen and insisted on getting a prescription for

00:18:45.940 --> 00:18:49.740
 progesterone or thyroid.

00:18:49.740 --> 00:18:55.220
 Just took a couple of years and doctors saw that their business was being affected and

00:18:55.220 --> 00:18:58.660
 so they totally reversed their practices.

00:18:58.660 --> 00:19:08.860
 And that went on until those doctors retired and then I think the pressure from the industry

00:19:08.860 --> 00:19:13.380
 and profession probably reverted the situation.

00:19:13.380 --> 00:19:15.500
 So it sounds like those doctors were pretty open-minded.

00:19:15.500 --> 00:19:18.140
 No, very, very closed-minded.

00:19:18.140 --> 00:19:19.140
 Okay.

00:19:19.140 --> 00:19:29.100
 I had a terrible experience of the first dozen or so women who went to them.

